    "The actions for Web tables include extracting data or column names, whereas for databases, the actions involve extracting table data or metadata.",
    "UniDM [36] manages a variety of data manipulation tasks, such as data cleaning, on data lakes through a three-action process.",
    "The first action is extracting context information, including table metadata and related records associated with the task, utilizing this information as demonstrations or background knowledge.",
    "The second action involves converting this context information into NL texts suitable for LLMs to reason.",
    "The final action employs prompt engineering to formulate the desired prompt."
